## 2. Integration with c_feature Pipeline

### Phase 4 (E2E Prep) Outputs

When native tests are required, Phase 4 must produce:

```
native_required: true
platforms: [ios, android]   # or just [ios] / [android]
groups: [A, B, E]           # which test groups to run
```

Use the decision matrix (Section 0) to determine these values.

### Phase 5 (Local E2E)

Run native tests in parallel with Playwright web tests:

```bash
# Native (separate terminal / background)
npm run test:native

# Or platform-specific
npm run test:native:ios
npm run test:native:android
```

Native and Playwright runners use **separate concurrency locks** (see Section 7) and can execute simultaneously.

### Phase 7 (DEV AWS E2E)

After deploy, run native tests against DEV AWS:

```bash
# Runner auto-discovers EC2 URL via AWS tag lookup
npm run test:native

# Or specify URL explicitly
./scripts/e2e/native-e2e-runner.sh --platform both --api-url http://ec2-X-X-X-X.compute-1.amazonaws.com:8080
```

