## 8. NPM Scripts

All native E2E scripts are defined in `package.json`:

| Script | Command | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `test:native` | `--platform both` | Run all native tests on iOS + Android |
| `test:native:ios` | `--platform ios` | Run native tests on iOS only |
| `test:native:android` | `--platform android` | Run native tests on Android only |
| `test:native:build` | `--build-only --platform both` | Build app for both platforms (no tests) |
| `test:native:build:ios` | `--build-only --platform ios` | Build app for iOS only |
| `test:native:build:android` | `--build-only --platform android` | Build app for Android only |

**Additional runner flags (direct invocation):**

```bash
# Rebuild app even if cached build exists
./scripts/e2e/native-e2e-runner.sh --platform ios --rebuild

# Dry run (validate config without executing)
./scripts/e2e/native-e2e-runner.sh --dry-run

# Run specific flows only
./scripts/e2e/native-e2e-runner.sh --platform ios --flows auth/login.yaml

# Specify backend URL explicitly
./scripts/e2e/native-e2e-runner.sh --platform both --api-url http://localhost:8080
```

